Dr. Park is the best! She is gentle and always makes sure I feel comfortable throughout my visit. She listens to my concerns and is very careful when treating me. Andrea, my dental hygienist, is also gentle and very good. They both understand my sensitivity issues and my pain aversion.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Warren Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJaBikqLI_jSFjGRQ69omCzi1e6w6AtO2eYaANGKKmUOYVdAQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Last Friday, I arrived about 15 minutes late, not realizing they have a 10-minute grace period—which is not industry standard. (Yes, they later said it was in the agreement I signed, but nobody remembers every one of those details.) I actually called them when I was about 10 minutes late and was already right outside the office, only to be told they could do a quick check-up but not the cleaning. So I told them to reschedule, and then I received a “no-show” notice.

Fast forward to today—I found out they had rescheduled my appointment for Tuesday, even though I told them multiple times that I wanted Wednesday instead. They coldly replied that I had “confirmed” the date, but I didn’t realize the date they sent me was for Tuesday rather than Wednesday. I assumed they were competent enough that I didn’t need to double-check every detail, but apparently I was wrong.

Now, because this is considered my second missed appointment—despite the miscommunication and poor handling on their side—they are charging me a $75 fee.

I have no issue honoring the terms I agreed to, but the way they treated me on the phone was extremely inhuman and showed zero empathy. It’s troubling to see a service provider treat clients not as people, but purely as transactions.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Wei-Lun Ting","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV75hsESjXSDm3w106_d63qhGTRgP5ynmgZO8anFbXZWazmgYM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had my first visit with Dr. Stella Park and was very impressed. She is extremely professional, patient, and thorough. She explained my gum health with detailed photos from the intraoral camera and performed the most careful and effective cleaning I’ve ever had. Highly recommended.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Robert Mico","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGvub7rnSgmpsKzqiP_a1CWO1d6MwbnZzEMeVpL2M2ZqjMvg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My family and I have been patients of Dr. Keith Baines for over 15 years, and I can honestly say he is an outstanding dentist. Dr. Baines is not only highly skilled, but he takes the time to explain how to properly care for our teeth, which has made a lasting difference in our dental health.

His work is top quality—he’s truly an artist, especially when it comes to bonding, crowns, fillings, and more. The results are always natural-looking and precise. You can tell he takes pride in his work and truly cares about his patients.

Family Dental has a welcoming, professional atmosphere, and it’s been a consistently positive experience over the years. The staff is always friendly, and the dental hygienist is phenomenal—thorough, gentle, and incredibly knowledgeable. His brother, Dr. Marshal Baines, is also part of the practice, and together they maintain a standard of excellence that’s hard to find.

Every visit feels like you’re stopping in to see friends—it’s that warm and personal. You’re not just a patient; you’re treated like family.

Highly recommend Dr. Keith Baines for anyone looking for a trustworthy and skilled dentist.

[{"Name":"Jerry Leung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLh1TqOs2izO41dJ4bTftNA7V1LNYm_tSiZiTwCIcgQcjf0Xw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here from a referral from a coworker after a horrible visit to another dental office. (Horrible is an understatement)
Was nice from the moment I walked thru the doors by a welcoming staff. Not by a generic, “hello, how are you?”. Staff was kind, soft spoken and especially patient.
I also wanted a 2nd opinion from another dentist, after the horrible 30sec exam I had at the last office.
Dr. Ellie (hope I spelled her name correctly) who examined me was so nice, so professional and she introduced herself! She took the time to completely explain everything to me, from diagnosis, the x-rays to future work that needed to be done, step by step. I’m not really an educated person, but she took the time to make sure I understood the situation with my teeth, instead of throwing big medical/dental terminology at me.
Although I left the place with bad news, (do NOT neglect your teeth ppl!!!) I left very happy and content, fully confident that I/my teeth was in good hands. Thank you Hudson Dental!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rron Bellcishta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWk0_-Czkc4MHUWIx-bocqaPWybLA_J7TTYo1W3aHsjX5Km_rK7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"12/10, I didn’t have to wait, the office was tidy and modern, and the staff hit the perfect balance between hospitable & professional. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chris Bright","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIr9zQYN-Be5rkI53wqpCpl7xKbzd8JK_VffQRyfuMlbYWv4Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"11/24 appt. I really wanted to like this office because the dentist I saw was very kind and the front desk staff is genuinely lovely, but the overall experience was incredibly frustrating.

I waited over an hour past my scheduled time because the dentist was still finishing another patient’s appointment. My own procedure then took much longer than expected, and when I finally left nearly two hours later, I received a call asking me to return because they had forgotten to take an impression of my bite. I went back, had the impressions done, and immediately afterward the temporary crown cracked, requiring me to return yet again.

I was told it would be five minutes, but in total I ended up spending three hours going in and out of this office for something that should have been handled correctly the first time. It is clear that patients dealing with urgent issues, especially those caused by the office’s own mistakes, are not prioritized.

The people are nice, but the disorganization and lack of attention to detail made this an exhausting and disappointing experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL0-LjZmUuxpUmvzTmVWr_pAss08zMEnqeYzqVC2cUbFI9_drQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I enjoyed the experience except for the x rays. Hard to find a dentist with top notch general and cosmetic care and feel like Dr. John is it!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Giovanni Fares","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLQEcWZy02WjzGoFu9fPoh_0g864PSSmKNybZf6HucT_2ovIyXA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As someone who is always constantly dreading the dentist. I made it my mission to find a place that was both kind and efficient while also understanding of my fears and needs when it comes to a dentist. From the moment that Cristina and I spoke on the phone I knew that this was going to be the place I chose to do my dental work. From her warm demeanor to her positive attitude I felt that I could accomplish anything and had nothing to be afraid of. I first came in to get a cleaning with Dr. Ari who is equally as kind and understanding the two of them aided in talking me through everything and helping me make the best decisions for my dental health. Immediately after my cleaning I felt comfortable enough to book my first procedure. However, when arriving my nerves were extremely heightened and I no longer felt comfortable that was until Cristina talked me through the whole process and made me feel comfortable, at ease and like I had nothing to worry about. This was the first time I had ever had a dental procedure without being medicated for my anxiety and that is completely and totally due to the kindness and patience of both Cristina and Dr. Ari. I am so happy that I chose soho smile and I can’t say I am looking forward to my next dental procedure but I also won’t say that am dreading it! Without Cristina I do not think I would have been able to go through with it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nora Eldasher","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKZPtOiUIF6YgmZ8vKbcYkMeEKjEXwORW1XBEhWs8VnqP54INon=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"From the moment I walked into Soho Smile, I knew I was in for a fantastic dental experience. From the welcoming reception area to the state-of-the-art treatment rooms, everything about this dental office exuded professionalism and care.

The staff at Soho Smile are truly exceptional. They greeted me with warm smiles and made me feel comfortable and at ease right away. The receptionist was friendly and efficient, making the check-in process a breeze. The dental assistants were equally attentive, patient and answered all my questions, ensuring I felt fully informed and confident.

Dr. John is undoubtedly one of the best dentists I've encountered. His expertise and professionalism for dentistry are evident in the way he meticulously examined my X-rays and walked me through his professional opinion. He took the time to listen to my concerns and provided me with a comprehensive explanation instead of rushing or pressuring me into making a decision.

I can't say enough good things about Soho Smile. My recent visit was truly an eye opening experience from start to finish. I typically had bad experience with dentist who are more concerned with making money than taking care of their patients, but that was not the case at Soho Smile. I will remain a patient at Soho Smile and do not see myself trusting or going to any other dentist in the future.

If you're looking for a dental office that combines expertise, compassion, and cutting-edge technology, Soho Smile is the place to go. I wholeheartedly recommend this practice to anyone seeking top-notch dental care in a warm and welcoming environment. They have certainly earned my trust and loyalty, and I look forward to my next visit.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"C G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKSFJijausa8WTV4H1msmUNxqUUScC8mtilTUWz6x0J3ffnNLM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"BEST experience everrr!! After getting consultations at a number of other dental offices, I chose Midtown Dental Care Associates because they offered the least invasive option at the best price, and they charged me and my insurance the most fairly for my consultation out of all of the offices.

I was nervous to get my first root canal, but Dr. Lynn did an excellent job and I felt no pain at all during the procedure. Dr. Stanescu put on a custom crown and made sure that the color matched perfectly with my other teeth.

Overall, I'm very satisfied with the services I got at this office. They are all super friendly, and they helped guide me through a traumatic experience to get a good outcome.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"David","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJvhX-xAWef0oijEVt7_q6P8HlSI9v08pI_I_5JRF128t7-D84=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have to remark that this clinic made a lasting positive impression on me that supersedes a transient concern I had, still being a student. I'm updating this review up one more, to the full five stars it deserves: I remember a time I wanted to provide someone in my own sphere such an experience at a time they needed it, but I was strongly discouraged to do so by a supervisor. I can only imagine if that supervisor had to be a dentist or hygienist, they wouldn't have very good reviews! Patients always know who is best, and this is a remarkable clinic.

[{"Name":"Jean-Claude Luu van Lang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZ8iETNvGDno--t4xj0mm4j9QcYrDv2BIlgW0E7vAGaP3z6A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice and helpful staff at the front desk. I was taken on time for my appointment. Dr Kepecs and her assistants are very caring, provide explanations about what they are doing and are open to answering any questions. The quality of the work is good. The only negative point is the duration of each appointment i have had (about 3 hours for a crown).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cenia Paredes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX24DDwng_CmQfC8eYxFKr6HuyxT5zohB3OGjYnaGoZtfxSs4fr=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was pleasantly surprised by the clean and pleasant appearance of this office. The staff was courteous and professional, although the hygienist was a bit rough. I particularly appreciated Dr. Kepecs. She was very pleasant, compassionate, and genuinely seemed to care about her patients.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jennifer Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXWOrbDAsI0WY7ROCY-PDENRL-l8CdEuytuTR-LGiTDvgojLtGd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went to NYC Dental - Upper East Side yesterday.  When I left, I circulated the following text: “it was an oddly good experience for having two teeth extracted.”

From the moment I stepped in, the energy was positive. The staff members were laughing with one another in a relaxed, clean, modern and beautifully-designed environment.

Dr. Behm and Dr. Danskin explained each part of the procedure and answered all of my questions. The surgery was swift and painless.  Afterward, I was given a QR-coded business card with Dr. Danskin’s aftercare instructions and her direct dial.

I initially went into their office after seeking a second opinion.  It was explained that my prior dentists should have never given me a root canal on a wisdom tooth. The extracted teeth should have been extracted years ago.

In addition, a week after having a perio rooting and scaling procedure in an unrelated dental office, there was still plaque on my teeth.  The staff explained that it may not be the prior dentist’s fault, but showed me unacceptable levels of plaque on the two teeth that were just removed.

It’s been less than 24 hours. There is minimal bleeding and pain (I never took the aspirin that was prescribed) thanks to the skilled hands of Dr. Danskin.

I am sending the entire staff my gratitude for such a wonderful experience.  Thank you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"José del Rosario","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK7RCmQJRwpE8cX3vPexK3glnlWhQhkqsRkCxkCqKbUtxwSLrqw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I cannot recommend NYC Dental on the Upper East Side enough! Dr. Kepecs is an exceptional dentist who has performed complicated dental work in my mouth with such skill and precision that I feel completely confident in her abilities. Beyond her technical expertise, her bedside manner is truly incredible—she makes you feel comfortable and cared for throughout every procedure. The entire staff reflects this same level of excellence, particularly Jackie, the front office manager, who is consistently friendly, professional, and always goes above and beyond to provide information and ensure every visit runs smoothly. From the moment you walk in until you leave, you're treated with genuine care and professionalism.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Erica Rosenfeld","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLK0rJ_ZfJ6kWlk46OCLyypS5N7riPqn-PD6tDQlSV2606Lw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been a patient at this office for many years.    I have always gotten great care from everyone from the front desk to the doctors and hygienists.  On my last visit I had Dr. Ariella fix one of my teeth and she did a great job.  The time before, Dr. Brandon fitted me with retainers that I wear every day and have helped me a lot.  I am a big fan of this office and I highly recommend it to anyone that is looking for great and high quality dental care.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aimee McBain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAP3Ajq6LBbBtd8_E6c8OrpwdPHSnWu4ahBaJ0ohPOfWvWgw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m certainly no fan of going to the dentist, but I cannot say enough good things about this practice. The staff is friendly, accommodating and compassionate. I’ve had to go multiple times recently for emergencies, and not only do they fit me in, but the head of the practice has been an absolute miracle worker! The office is modern and clean. I cannot thank them enough ❤️","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"meshachb","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKMbBB6D6-QsPibP1apr3Qu54mgzFfkSQoIER773NqfhcCh2w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Jackie was very welcoming and my dentist walked me through all my options while helping me decide on the best treatment option for me. (thank you Dr Weinstock and Dr Behm for your care)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elaine Kang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBo_5y94M9Bt9yHygMS0lAn4yu6l9RTCqKssy2Xn4IUZ6mHsE3nA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Remer is excellent and fully explains everything so you can understand what is going on. Best Dental practice ever!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nikolaus Kriegeskorte","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVxasqJ_FVMdyIsdRzrcolZiX2pKZftRsLJnf7VXaCKpMo_el_x=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"After being quite satisfied with this practice for a couple of years, I lost trust through a sequence of three incidents. First, they suggested a treatment that cost a few hundred dollars not covered by my Aetna insurance. I trusted them that it was medically advisable and paid for it. Then during a checkup, they found a cavity and told me that removing it would not be covered by my insurance and would cost a couple of hundred dollars. This was puzzling to me, because cavities should be covered by even the most basic dental insurance plan. I decided to cancel the appointment for this treatment. Then for my hygiene appointment soon after, they told me that (in contrast to the previous hygiene appointments at this practice) it would cost a couple of hundred dollars out of pocket, since the insurance only provided a minimal contribution. At that point I canceled the appointment and went to a different dental practice. At my new dental practice, a $30 co-pay covered hygiene, xrays, and checkup, the service was outstanding, the dentist took ample time to discuss all potential issues, and told me I had no cavities.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"thomas w schaller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfdM8MDXsLRpd0RJBLuNWIXkIewLyABsDa-yf4g2Kg32vELmtVNg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Not many love going to the dentist, but Midtown Dental Group makes the experience surprisingly pleasant . [{"Name":"Daria Dmitrochenko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRbbqcHS5qbmPVxNNXEG8LvYkAUgzvXZrlC4E3LiDy3r84nHHy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve had the best dental cleaning of my life. It was thorough, significantly improved the look of my teeth, and I barely felt anything.

My husband had an emergency tooth extraction, and Dr. Armstrong was wonderful with him. She also did my dental exam and never pushed any unnecessary procedures—she simply gave her professional opinion and reassured me when I was worried about my husband.

The front desk staff are polite, personable, and accommodating. They work with most major insurance providers and clearly explain in advance what may not be covered, so there are no surprises.

Overall, it was a wonderful experience, and I cannot recommend this clinic enough.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Usman Ghani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJyVNAI2NWG6bh2OEJrh9yv73e-bkkj2BCcvzeYimW2q5jgiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Dr. Sullivan’s dental clinic and had an excellent experience from start to finish. The staff was welcoming, professional, and made me feel comfortable right away. Dr. Sullivan took the time to explain everything clearly and answered all of my questions with patience. The clinic itself was clean, modern, and very well-organized.

The care I received was thorough yet gentle, and I truly felt like I was in good hands. It’s not always easy to feel relaxed at the dentist, but Dr. Sullivan and the team created such a calm and friendly environment. I left the appointment feeling very satisfied with the results and confident about continuing my dental care here.

I highly recommend Dr. Sullivan’s clinic to anyone looking for quality dental care and a team that genuinely cares about their patients.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"C G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLqOYz3QEvFuDYpFWXU7_JdecW70lkyovR7DfGxzV0KTp6Gyw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Armstrong and the practice office are great.  I visited to take care of a broken tooth and needed an extraction.   Dr. Armstrong is intolerable and confident and that made me feel very calm.  I am very happy with the procedure and the practice overall !  Great communications every step of the way, and the office was spotless and very pleasant.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joe W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIPYOPN2sFI2l73cHYuGiGCfezYs9JDvuq8VsHYodXqo1aLJS-f=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was a new patient. I went in for a 6 month cleaning. As a new patient, x-rays were taken of my teeth, as I would expect. The dentist then looked at my teeth. My teeth were not cleaned by a hygienist. The dentist did the procedure. He clearly had somewhere else to go because he only spent five minutes cleaning my teeth before sending me on my way. FIVE MINUTES.

Add to this, there was music blaring in the waiting room and the examination room. It was the most unprofessional medical experience I’ve ever had.

The only redeeming aspect of the visit was the woman at the front desk. She was quite pleasant. She also seemed surprised I was done so quickly.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nina Rivera","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgcSdlxwnecpdnSts1HP-vImz3V9JR-p-nZuof1bPlI9ankpQp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had my preventive maintenance cleaning today and Violet was very thorough and educated me on the importance of using floss, water picks an other dental tools to prevent inflammation and bacteria , especially since I have a bridge.  The cleaning was very thorough and both Violet and Dr. Kay were very knowledgeable and friendly.  The office staff was also friendly, letting me know what my insurance can /cannot cover.

I have been going here for years and this level of service was top tier. I 10/10 recommend Midtown Dental Group for all of your dental needs.  I am in good hands, and I am sure you will be too!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Moshe Markovich","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVI1Zpr5dYwpwlmMLf5NRrpf4v1IDv1_t3BTU5Zx73MjxtQgqYVBg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had two veneers done at Midtown Dental Group and I genuinely couldn’t be happier with the entire experience. It’s clear she genuinely cares about her patients and the results speak for themselves.

The office is welcoming, and run by a fantastic team who make you feel comfortable from the moment you walk in. On top of all that, the pricing is fair and transparent.

There’s a reason Midtown Dental Group keeps expanding. They’re simply the best. If you’re looking for top-tier dental care in NYC, this is the place. Thank you Dr. Armstrong and team!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jineara Hampton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbAfkgR4_fGbafajW4xr8tgeI-8Qhlq5N9HoLTRKOtZhsnRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Best Dental care I had in years !!!
